{"id":14881286,"mediaExerciseId":"c215e2d1-f11d-4b92-88f4-c53f0561b732","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"11","chapterTitle":"Project Analysis and Evaluation","groupId":612351,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":375,"solutions":[{"id":6058796,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Forecasting risk refers to the type of risk wherein the predictions on certain elements of the market are not true. This may affect the possible profits or losses since there are many factors that can affect the forecasting of the prices.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"In general, a new product will have a higher forecasting risk compared to a cost-cutting product since there is not much data yet on the performance of the new product. For the cost-cutting product, the factors are already known which makes the lowering of its forecasting risk easier. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"87c9bb6a-d505-4bd7-8ebd-017694f55a5d","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14